{
  "texts": [
    "Each category has its community, which is in charge of keeping Log(n) table up-to-date.",
    "The blockchain stores the unique ID of each source.",
    "Equation ( 6) expresses the retrieval of data into physically existing nodes.",
    "So this is used to determine the distance between two nodes, where S indicates the data categories used to collect data from the sources.",
    "Furthermore, the weight matrix characteristics for the nodes s i and s j are (x * s i pq + s j pq), and data is extracted by measuring the distance between two nodes d i ( s i,s j)."
